The paper focuses on optimizing the performance of OpenCL kernels, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper presents case studies on 2D convolution and matrix multiplication, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV) and linear algebra (cs.LA). The paper also discusses the use of search strategies such as simulated annealing and particle swarm optimization, which are topics related to artificial intelligence and robotics (cs.AR) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the auto-tuner, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
